  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Safeguarding the Minaret and Archaeological Remains of Jam, Afghanistan - Phase I</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project will elaborate a detailed conservation plan for the Minaret, focusing on overall protection, structural stability and monitoring; install a monitoring system; and undertake actual works to safeguard the structure. The Project will also include a strong mentoring component, as it will be implemented through the direct involvement of relevant Afghan authorities and Universities, thereby creating the conditions for its sustainability with a direct beneficial impact on local professionals. Selected experts will work on a continuous basis with a team of Afghan professionals from the Ministries and Universities, thereby providing a significant opportunity to enhance local capacities.</narrative>
  </description>
